#Text=Wikinews Shorts : March 29 , 2007
#Text=A compilation of brief news reports for Thursday , March 29 , 2007 .
#Text=Flaming debris nearly hits LAN airliner
#Text=A LAN Airlines Airbus A340 was making its approach into Auckland when incandescent objects flew by at super-sonic speeds .
#Text=Australian and New Zealand media initially reported that it was debris from a Russian satellite breaking up during re-entry .
#Text=NASA said it was more likely to be meteors .
#Text=The Civil Aviation Authority of New Zealand is set to investigate the incident .
#Text=Sources
#Text=Peter Lewis .
#Text=" Burning Russian space junk whizzes past Auckland-bound plane " — Australian Broadcasting Corporation , March 29 , 2007
#Text=" ' Flaming debris ' nearly hits jet " — BBC News Online , March 29 , 2007
#Text=North Korea asks for food aid
#Text=According to an official for World Food Programme ( WFP ) , North Korea has admitted that the country faces food shortages and needs help .
#Text=WFP is appealing to donor countries to step up aid , and to the UN to keep food aid outside of the nuclear debate .
#Text=Food donations dropped dramatically after North Korea carried out its nuclear test bombing .
#Text=North Korea 's shortage may be approaching 20 % of what it needs to feed its people .
#Text=Sources
#Text=" North Korea admits food shortages " — BBC News Online , March 28 , 2007
#Text=Lindsay Beck .
#Text=" North Korea desperate for aid amid nuclear woes -UN " — Reuters , March 28 , 2007
#Text=Man killed during hooligans clashes in Athens
#Text=A 25 year old man was killed during clashes between fans of Olympiacos and Panathinaikos in the suburb of Peania , in east Athens .
#Text=The victim died at a central hospital from several injuries he suffered .
#Text=The fight happened prior to a local women volleyball game in Peania .
#Text=However , witnesses and residents told Alter Channel that the clashes had no relation with the game but were pre-organized by hooligan clubs in the area .
#Text=The event caused political turbulent in Greece as long as Greek police and the Minister of Public Order have been accused by some media for their failure to prevent fans ' clashes .
#Text=Sources
#Text=Athens News Agency .
#Text=" Bitter Clashes Claim One Life " — Elliniki Radiofonia Tileorasi , March 29 , 2007
#Text=Associated Press .
#Text=" 1 dead , 5 hurt in violence at Greek women 's volleyball game " — International Herald Tribune , March 29 , 2007
#Text=Senate passes spending bill with withdrawal date
#Text=Despite a veto threat from US President Bush , the US Senate today passed a spending bill that includes a time-table for a US withdrawal from Iraq .
#Text=Passing 51-47 , the legislation echoes that passed recently by the House .
#Text=It sets a goal of pulling all combat troops out of Iraq by the end of March 2008 , without explicitly demanding their removal .
#Text=Related news
#Text=" Wikinews Shorts : March 27 , 2007 " — Wikinews , March 27 , 2007
#Text=Sources
#Text=" Senate backs Iraq withdrawal date " — BBC News Online , March 29
#Text=Richard Cowan .
#Text=" Senate approves ' 08 goal to bring troops home " — Reuters , March 29 , 2007
#Text=Further escalation of sectarian violence in Iraq
#Text=A series of bombings in Bagdhad and Khalis in Iraq killed as many as 130 people .
#Text=The areas targeted were mainly Shia and many victims were women and children in market places .
#Text=Prime Minister of Iraq Nouri al-Maliki condemned the attacks and called for restraint , urging Iraqis to work with security forces to prevent the violence getting out of control .
#Text=Sources
#Text=Ahmed Rasheed .
#Text=" Suicide bombers kill 130 in Iraq " — Reuters , March 29 , 2007
#Text=" Multiple bombs target Iraqi Shia " — BBC News Online , March 29 , 2007
